cs.NE, cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.PF 

The paper deals with optimization problems in stochastic networks, which involve resource allocation. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) which deals with optimization problems, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) which deals with distributed systems and networks, cs.IT (Information Theory) which deals with communication and information in networks, cs.SY (Systems and Control) which deals with control and optimization of systems, and cs.PF (Performance) which deals with performance analysis of systems.
